Decode Images¶

To make sure that the model produces reasonable results we plotted the decoded images to compare them with the original image.

In [7]:
# decode images
pred_test = autoencoder.predict(x_test[:20])
In [8]:
# definition to show original image and reconstructed image
def showDecodedImages(orig, dec, num=10):
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    n = num
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 4))

    for i in range(n):
        # display original
        ax = plt.subplot(2, n, i+1)
        plt.imshow(orig[i].reshape(32, 32, 3))
        ax.get_xaxis().set_visible(False)
        ax.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)

        # display reconstruction
        ax = plt.subplot(2, n, i +1 + n)
        plt.imshow(dec[i].reshape(32, 32, 3))
        ax.get_xaxis().set_visible(False)
        ax.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)
    plt.show()
In [9]:
showDecodedImages(x_test, pred_test)

Latent Space as SPLOM¶

To make sure that the distribution of the extracted features is reasonable continuous we plotted them pairwise as a scatter plot matrix. As shown in the SPLOM the Distributions are seemingly "well behaved" without any obvious steps.

In [10]:

y_test_random = y_test[sample_ids]

# encode the images and convert the latent space to a data frame
pred_test_random = encoder.predict(x_test_random)

Latent Space as UMAP Projection¶

The UMAP Projection reduced the 10-dimensional latent space into 2 dimensions by simultaneously preserve the maximum of the original variance. This allows us to plot the encoded images as a scatter plot. The projection shows that while no distinct clusters are visible a tendency of images of the same class appearing together is clearly visible.

In [12]:
# encode the images and convert the latent space to a data frame
pred_test = encoder.predict(x_test) 
pred_test = pd.DataFrame(pred_test).iloc[:, : 10]

# project encoded images on a 2D surface
umap.plot.output_notebook()
mapper = umap.UMAP().fit(pred_test)
p = umap.plot.interactive(mapper, labels= y_test.flatten(),  point_size=4)
umap.plot.show(p)
